    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with a high-floor lineup, led by the elite pairing of **Gunnar Henderson** (83.29) and **Kyle Tucker** (77.88). **Gunnar Henderson** is the clear standout; his role at the top of the order combined with a 4.61 xERA matchup against Wacha generates significant run-scoring potential. We are also capitalizing on high-leverage spots for **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (74.56), **Luis Robert Jr.** (74.29), and **Jackson Merrill** (75.10). **Jackson Merrill** specifically benefits from an elite park factor (+14%) and a favorable matchup against Sugano, making him a prime candidate for multi-hit production. **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** and **Brady House** are both projected for strong days against Fuentes, as the 5.07 xERA provides a clear lane for our offense to exploit the bottom of the pitching rotation.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench involved **Marcell Ozuna** (60.82), who graded out as a strong start but was ultimately squeezed out by the efficiency of our outfield and utility spots. While **Marcell Ozuna** carries significant power, the calculated platoon advantages for **Miguel Vargas** and the positional necessity of keeping **Drake Baldwin** in the C1 slot forced him to the pine. We are monitoring **Jacob Wilson** closely; his score of 40.47 is the lowest in the starting lineup, a direct result of facing an elite arm in Gilbert (2.86 xERA). If the lineup remains tight, we may look to pinch-hit **Nolan Schanuel** or **Josh Jung** late in the game if the situation demands a high-contact replacement. Overall, the squad is well-positioned, though we remain vigilant regarding any last-minute weather shifts that could impact the run-scoring environments for **Andy Pages** and the rest of the outfield.",
